{
  "texts": [
    "The integration of verification mechanisms, which crossreference generated content with trusted data sources, has been shown to curb the incidence of hallucinations significantly [27,3].",
    "Implementing feedback loops where models are regularly updated based on their performance in real-world applications helps in identifying and correcting patterns leading to hallucinations [31,32,33,27,34].",
    "The use of constrained generation techniques, which limit the model's ability to generate content outside certain factual boundaries, has also been effective [34,35,36,37].",
    "Enhancing the models' understanding of context and causality has led to more coherent and accurate text generation [27,38,39].",
    "Research has pointed towards the utility of ensemble methods, combining the outputs of multiple models to filter out hallucinated content [40,41,42]."
  ]
}